## No-Guessing Rules

These are mandatory. No exceptions, no "reasonable defaults."

- If you haven't read the file, you do not know its contents. Read it first.
- If a field name, function signature, or type is not confirmed by a file
  you actually read, do not use it.
- If a test does not fail before you write code, you have not written the
  correct test.
- If information is missing, ask. Do not assume.
- "The user already explained the context" is not equivalent to reading the file.

